{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Review Protections for Children Against Coercive Control in Family Court Process",
        "additional_details": "We believe that children are often not properly heard in family court, leaving them distressed and unheard in decisions affecting their lives. The process can be emotionally damaging, with repeated hearings and forced contact causing long-term harm. When coercive control is overlooked, it can affect a child\u2019s mental health, development, and future relationships. Stronger protections are needed to ensure children\u2019s voices matter and their wellbeing is prioritised.",
        "background": "Review safeguards in family courts to address coercive control, to ensure children\u2019s voices are heard, and prioritise their wellbeing. Improve training, guidance, and use of supervised contact where manipulation or emotional harm is identified.",
